hopobject.body: this is be cool 8) nla for her live lean stack reviews PayPal was developed to allow customers of online auction site eBay to pay for goods without having to enter credit card details for each transaction, but it has since grown to a payments service that aims to rival Mastercard and Visa. It is now accepted online by major retailers including John Lewis. Merchants say the standard online service is popular because it replaces the laborious process of entering 16-digit credit or debit card numbers, plus additional passwords, with a single user name and password.
